The paper deals with the problem of constructing a communication infrastructure for wireless nodes, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses distributed algorithms, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC). The scheduling of links in the SINR model involves information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions efficiency in terms of the number of slots used, which could be related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
